cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.HC 

This paper discusses the analysis of textual data captured by lifelogging devices, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of semantic analysis tools, which falls under the category of machine learning (ML) and information retrieval (IR), making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also discusses the potential use of wearable devices, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (HCI), making cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the quantification of cognitive activity, which falls under the category of cybernetics (CY), making cs.CY a possible sub-category as well.
